34 A.3d 498 ATTORNEY GRIEVANCE COMMISSION OF MARYLAND, Petitioner v. Thomas D. WALL, Respondent. Misc. Docket AG No. 46,

Sept. Term, 2011.

Court of Appeals of Maryland. Dec. 21, 2011.

ORDER

The Court of Appeals of Maryland, having considered the Joint Petition of the Attorney Grievance Commission and Respondent, Thomas D. Wall, to place Respondent on Inactive Status By Consent pursuant to Maryland Rule 16-772, it is this 21st day of December, 2011;

ORDERED, that the Joint Petition be, and it is hereby GRANTED, and the Respondent, Thomas D. Wall, is hereby placed on Inactive Status by consent; and,

ORDERED, that the Clerk of this Court shall remove the name of Thomas D. Wall from the register of attorneys in the Court and certify that fact to the Client Protection Fund of the Bar of Maryland and all Clerks of all judicial tribunals in this State in accordance with Maryland Rule 16-772(d).
